er Creek, New York|Beecher Creek]]\n| Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1998.<ref name=\"nris\"/>\n|-\n| [[Blenheim Bridge]]\n| [[File:BlenheimBridge HAER cropped.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Schoharie County, New York|Schoharie County]]\n| 1855\n| 232 \n| [[Schoharie Creek]]\n| Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1966 and [[National Historic Landmark]] in 1964.<ref name=\"nris\"/> Destroyed on August 28, 2011, by [[Hurricane Irene (2011)|Tropical Storm Irene]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/01/us/01bridges.html?src=me&ref=us |title=Covered Bridges, Beloved Remnants of Another Era, Were Casualties, Too |author=Eckholm, Erik |date=August 31, 2011 |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=2011-09-02}}</ref> Rebuilt in 2017-2018.\n|-\n| [[Beaverkill Bridge]], also known as Conklin Bridge\n| [[File:Beaverkill Covered Bridge.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Sullivan County, New York|Sullivan County]]\n| 1865\n| 98\n| [[Beaver Kill]]\n| Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2007.<ref name=\"nris\"/>\n|-\n| [[Bendo Bridge]], or Willowemoc Covered Bridge\n| [[File:Bendo Bridge Apr 11.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Sullivan County, New York|Sullivan County]]\n| 1860\n| 48\n| [[Willowemoc Creek]]\n| <!-- notes -->\n|-\n| [[Halls Mills Bridge]]\n| [[File:Halls Mills Bridge Apr 11.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Sullivan County, New York|Sullivan County]]\n| 1912\n| 119\n| [[Neversink River]]\n| <!-- notes -->\n|-\n| [[Van Tran Flat Bridge]], formerly called the Mott's Flat Bridge and also known as the Livingston Manor Bridge\n| [[File:VAN TRAN FLAT COVERED BRIDGE.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Sullivan County, New York|Sullivan County]]\n| 1860\n| 117\n| [[Willowemoc Creek]]\n| <!-- notes -->\n|-\n| [[Newfield Bridge]]\n| [[File:Newfield Covered Bridge Feb 10.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Tompkins County, New York|Tompkins County]]\n| 1853\n| 115\n| [[Cayuga Creek]]\n| Listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2000.<ref name=\"nris\"/>\n|-\n| [[Ashokan 