August 2008}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* Dale J. Travis Covered Bridges. [http://www.dalejtravis.com/cblist/cbny.htm NYSCB Credits]. Retrieved May 20, 2013.\n* Covered Bridges of the Northeast USA. [http://www.coveredbridgesite.com/ny/ny_home.html NYSCB Credits]. Retrieved May 20, 2013.\n\n==External links==\n{{GeoGroupTemplate}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070629172410/http://www.nycoveredbridges.org/page6.html \"Overview of the History of Covered Bridges in New York State\" by Raymond Smith]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:New York covered bridges}}\n[[Category:Covered bridges in New York (state)|*]]\n[[Category:Landmarks in New York (state)|Covered bridges]]\n[[Category:New York (state) transportation-related lists|Covered bridges]]\n[[Category:Lists of covered bridges in the United States]]\n[[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in New York (state)|Bridges]]\n", "name_user": "Waz8", "label": "safe", "comment": "combine both external links sections", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_covered_bridges_in_New_York"}
{"title_page": "Nova Scotia killings", "text_new": "{{short description|Series of shootings in Nova Scotia, Canada}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title            = Nova Scotia killings\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord            = {{coord|45.1965|-63.3377}}\n|  zoom            = 7\n| float            = center\n| width            = 300\n| height           = 206\n| caption          =\n|   title          =\n|    minimap       = file\n|  mini-file       = Canada_location_map.svg\n| mini-width       = 120\n|mini-height       = 64\n|  minipog-x       = 105\n|  minipog-y       = 48\n|  scalemark       = 120 <!-- shifts the scalemark further to the left -->\n|      shape1      = image\n|       mark1      = Red pog.svg\n|      label1      = Portapique, Nova Scotia\n| mark-coord1      = {{coord|45.4015|-63.6977}} \n|  label-pos1      = bottom\n| label-size1      = 10\n|label-color1      = black\n| label-offset-x1  =\n| label-offset-y1  =\n|mark-title1       = Portapique, NS\n|mark-image1       =\n|mark-description1 =\n|      label2      = Enfield, Nova Scotia\n|       mark2      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size2       = 8\n|  label-pos2      = left\n| label-size2      = 10\n|label-color2      = black\n| mark-coord2      = {{coord|44.9274|-63.5366}}\n|mark-title2       = Enfield, NS\n}}\n| partof           = \n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = Portapique in Nova Scotia\n| susperp          = \n| location         = [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| target           = \n| date             = {{start date|2020|4|18}} \u2013 <br />{{end date|2020|4|19}}\n| time             = \n| timezone         = [[UTC\u221203:00]]\n| coordinates      = \n| type             = [[Spree shooting]], [[arson]], [[mass murder]]\n| weapons          = Firearm, fire\n| fatalities       = At least 17 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries         = At least 1\n| victim           = \n| perp             = Gabriel Wortman<ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|title=At least 16 people dead after N.S. gunman's rampage, and police say toll could grow|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n| numparts         = \n| numpart          = \n| dfens            = \n| dfen             = \n| footage          = \n| motive           = \n}}\n\nA [[spree killing]] comprised of [[shooting]]s and [[Arson|arsons]] took place in the [[Canada|Canadian]] province of [[Nova Scotia]], between April 18 and 19, 2020. A man identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman killed at least 16 people, including a [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) officer, before another officer killed him following a car chase.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman>{{Cite news|title=At Least 13 Killed in Nova Scotia Shooting, Police Say|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|last=Diaz|first=Johnny|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|last2=Bilefsky|first2=Dan|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> It was the deadliest attack of its kind in Canadian history.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|title=Gunman kills 16 in rampage, deadliest in Canadian history|last=Gillies|first=Rob|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Killings==\nOn the evening of April 18, police responded to multiple [[9-1-1]] calls regarding a gun-related incident in the small community of [[Portapique]], {{convert|130|km|mi}} north of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]].<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|title=Timeline: How an active-shooter situation unfolded in Nova Scotia|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/canadian-authorities-say-mass-shooting-suspect-may-have-been-disguised-n1187381|title=Canadian authorities say at least 10 people, including officer, killed in mass shooting|last1=Madani|first1=Doha|last2=Stelloh|first2=Tim|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|title=Nova Scotia mass killings: What we know and what we don't know|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> They found several dead and injured inside and outside a home, but not the suspect.<ref name=\"ABC\">{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/multiple-victims-canada-shooting-suspect-dressed-police-officer/story?id=70232582|title=16 dead, including police officer, in deadliest shooting in Canadian history|last=Deliso|first=Meredith|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe investigation overnight led police to many crime scenes that were ultimately scattered over at least {{convert|50|km|mi}}.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /> At around 8:00 a.m. on April 19, police announced on [[Twitter]] that they were dealing with an [[active shooter]] situation. Residents were advised by the RCMP to stay indoors, while a portion of the town was evacuated.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"MassLive\">{{cite news|url=https://www.masslive.com/news/2020/04/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman-kills-16-including-police-officer-in-canadas-deadliest-shooting-attack.html|title=Nova Scotia shooting: Gabriel Wortman kills 16 including police officer in Canada's deadliest shooting attack|publisher=MassLive|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Three buildings and two cars were reported burning, which required a firefighter response.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CTV\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shot-and-killed-by-police-1.4902687|title=Gunman killed 16 people in rampage in N.S.; deadliest such attack in Canada: police|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nGabriel Wortman was identified as the shooter at 8:54 a.m. A [[Manhunt (law enforcement)|manhunt]] ensued, and around two hours later, the public was warned that he may be posing as an RCMP officer and operating a vehicle made to look like an RCMP cruiser,<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6840120/nova-scotia-shooting-timeline/|title=Timeline of what we know about Nova Scotia killing spree that left RCMP officer, 16 others dead|publisher=Global News|last=Shah|first=Maryam|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref> and that he was travelling on Highway 4 near [[Glenholme]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|title=A timeline of the deadly shooting incident in Nova Scotia|last=Lopez-Martinez|first=Melissa|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Residents were urged to avoid the area.<ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s>{{Cite news|title=17 dead, including one RCMP officer, after shooting spree in Portapique, N.S.|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|last=Quon|first=Alexander|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=[[Global News]]|last2=Stephenson|first2=Mercedes}}</ref> Police tweeted to the public to call 9-1-1 immediately if they spotted the vehicle.<ref name=\"ABC\" /> Another hour later, they said he switched to a silver [[Chevrolet Tracker]] [[sports utility vehicle]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|title=Canada shooting: Gunman kills at least 16 in rural Canada|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSightings of Wortman were confirmed in [[Debert]], [[Brookfield, Nova Scotia|Brookfield]], and [[Milford (Halifax), Nova Scotia|Milford]].<ref name=\"CTV\" /> Nearly twelve hours after police first received the firearms complaint,<ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2020/4/19/21227349/mass-shooting-nova-scotia-canada-enfield-portapique|title=What we know about a mass shooting in Nova Scotia, Canada|publisher=Vox|last=Collins|first=Sean|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Wortman was killed by police outside a gas station restaurant at the [[Irving Oil]] Big Stop in [[Enfield, Nova Scotia|Enfield]], about {{convert|92|km|mi}} south of Portapique and about {{convert|40|km|mi}} north of Halifax.<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" />\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe shooter was identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman, whom [[CBC News]] described as a [[denturist]] working in the Halifax area. He owned real estate in Portapique and [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]].<ref name=\"CBC\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-gunman-profile-quiet-gentle-denturist|title=Nova Scotia shooting: shock at killings by 'quiet, gentle' denturist|first=Leyland|last=Cecco|date=April 20, 2020|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Victims==\nAt least 16 people were killed, one of them a veteran RCMP officer, Constable Heidi Stevenson. A second RCMP officer was injured and is in stable condition.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s /> According to Commissioner [[Brenda Lucki]], some of the first victims had connections to Wortman, but as the killings continued, the targets became more random.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/> The victims are believed to have died from gunshot wounds, but other causes are also being investigated.<ref name=\"CBC3\" />\n\n==Reactions==\nNova Scotia Premier [[Stephen McNeil]] told reporters, \"This is one of the most senseless acts of violence in our province's history.\" He expressed his condolences to the residents affected and the families of the victims.<ref name=\"CTV2\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/shooting-one-of-the-most-senseless-acts-of-violence-in-nova-scotia-s-history-premier-1.4902917|title=Shooting 'one of the most senseless acts of violence' in Nova Scotia's history: premier|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] also expressed his condolences.<ref name=\"CBC\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]]\n* [[Moncton shooting]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in North America]]\n[[Category:2020s mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Canada]]\n[[Category:Attacks in 2020]]\n[[Category:Crime in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Death in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Canada]]\n[[Category:Royal Canadian Mounted Police]]\n[[Category:Spree shootings in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Series of shootings in Nova Scotia, Canada}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title            = Nova Scotia killings\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord            = {{coord|45.1965|-63.3377